      "content": "When it comes to high-stakes dinner etiquette, a client should aim to dress conservatively yet elegantly, avoiding anything too flashy or bold. For men, this typically means a tailored suit, crisp white shirt, and a tie, while women should opt for a slim-fitting cocktail dress or a pantsuit in a neutral color palette. At the dinner table, keep your hands visible, use your napkin to wipe your mouth, and avoid playing with your phone or other objects. Also, be mindful of the table settings and use the correct utensils for the course being served.",
